Three new species of the millipede genus Hyleoglomeris Verhoeff, 1910 from the Aegean region of Greece (Diplopoda, Glomerida, Glomeridae)Abstract Three new cavernicolous species of Hyleoglomeris are described from Greece: Hyleoglomeris subreducta sp.n., from Chios Island, Hyleoglomeris translucida sp.n., from Rhodes Island, and Hyleoglomeris insularis sp.n., from Kalymnos Island, all in the Aegean Sea.